課程概述 Course Description
       教導神經論文寫作的基本概念、技巧，以口授、練習寫作並由授課老師批改等方式交替進行，藉此培養日後發表論文之寫作能力。•To improve the writing skills of PhD students.
•To improve the presentation skills of PhD students.
•To improve powerpoint presentation/and learn endnote
    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
To improve the writing skills of PhD students.To improve the presentation skills of PhD students.To improve powerpoint presentation/and learn endnote 

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Class I: general introduction and communication (Feb 17)2Class II: powerpoint presentation/endnote (Feb 24)33/3 background introduction of your topics/labs, your preliminary data (preliminary results >1 page/introduction > 1 page/ references > 5)43/10 background introduction of your topics/labs, your preliminary data (preliminary results >1 page/introduction > 1 page/ references > 5)53/17 background introduction of your topics/labs, your preliminary data (preliminary results >1 page/introduction > 1 page/ references > 5)6Classes in Scientific Writing (March 31)74月 presenting your outlines (title, 1 page/abstract, 1 page/Specific aims (2-4) and hypothesis (1 paragraph, 1 page, references > 10) 84月 ppresenting your outlines (title, 1 page/abstract, 1 page/Specific aims (2-4) and hypothesis (1 paragraph, 1 page, references > 10) 94月 ppresenting your outlines (title, 1 page/abstract, 1 page/Specific aims (2-4) and hypothesis (1 paragraph, 1 page, references > 10) 104月 ppresenting your outlines (title, 1 page/abstract, 1 page/Specific aims (2-4) and hypothesis (1 paragraph, 1 page, references > 10) 11May classes for presenting your research design and methods (rationale, experimental approaches, data analysis for each aim/sub-aim, > 2 pages, references > 15)12May classes for presenting your research design and methods (rationale, experimental approaches, data analysis for each aim/sub-aim, > 2 pages, references > 15)13May classes for presenting your research design and methods (rationale, experimental approaches, data analysis for each aim/sub-aim, > 2 pages, references > 15)14May classes for presenting your research design and methods (rationale, experimental approaches, data analysis for each aim/sub-aim, > 2 pages, references > 15)15May 26, polish your Abstract for the June 1 deadline16June classes: rwriting and presentation17June classes:  writing and presentation18June classes: writing and presentation 

